            <p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/companies/square-enix">Square Enix</a> is finally releasing <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/final-fantasy-7-remake-review-a-faithful-remake-with-a-few-missteps-along-the-way">Final Fantasy 7 Remake</a> and Rebirth as a physical double pack.</p>
<p>These games are the first two parts of the Remake trilogy, which reimagines the original PS1 classic <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/final-fantasy-vii">Final Fantasy 7</a>.</p>
<p>Available from 4th December exclusively on PS5, the <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/final-fantasy-7-remake-intergrade">Final Fantasy 7 Remake Intergrade</a> and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-guides-tips-tricks-9403">Final Fantasy 7 Rebirth</a> Twin Pack Physical Edition (as it's known) will cost $59.99 / €69.99 / £59.99. You can pre-order it now from the <a href="https://gb.store.square-enix-games.com/final-fantasy-vii-remake-intergrade-_-rebirth---twin-pack-physical-edition?_gl=1%2Alcp8u1%2A_gcl_au%2AMjM5MjUyNTcuMTc1NjcxNjY0MQ..&amp;_ga=2.95225759.2068626468.1760015048-116765061.1756716641">Square Enix store</a>.</p>

